definition.value: A perfluorinated compound in which the carbon chain atoms are completely fluorinated.
A steroid sulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate functions of alpha-muricholic acid 7-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion that results from the deprotonation of both of the carboxylic acid groups of itaconic acid.
The conjugate base of tauro-alpha-muricholic acid obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid sulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate functions of glycocholic acid 7-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.

Any compound formally derived from an isoprenoid by loss of a methylene group. Norisoprenoids are a diverse class of aromatic compounds that contribute to the varietal character of many wines, especially in aromatic varieties such as Riesling.
A N-acylheptadecasphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as octadecanoyl.
An organofluorine compound that has multiple fluorine atoms attached to an alkyl chain (but at least one of the carbon atoms in the chain is not fully fluorinated).
The mono(2-ethylhexyl) ester of benzene-1,2-dicarboxylic acid.
